definitions.definition: carry out or put into effect (a plan, order, or course of action).
examples: the corporation executed a series of financial deals
synonyms: conduct; Moreinformalpull off; formaleffectuate "the corporation executed a series of financial deals"

examples: not only does she execute embroideries, she designs them, too

definitions.definition: perform (an activity or maneuver requiring care or skill).
examples: they had to execute their dance steps with the greatest precision

definitions.definition: make (a legal instrument) valid by signing or sealing it.
carry out (a judicial sentence, the terms of a will, or other order).
carry out an instruction or program.
carry out a sentence of death on (a legally condemned person).
examples: he was convicted of treason and executed
synonyms: put before a firing squad; informalstring up
